juniMRouterAgent.name: juniMRouterAgent

revisions.description: Extended the ipMRouteInterfaceEntry Table, introduced traps and platform dependent rsMRoutePortTable.
Scalar attribute rsMcastRpfDisable is supported for the Juniper-MROUTER-MIB.
Replaced Unisphere names with Juniper names. Added support for the Juniper-MROUTER-MIB.
The initial release of this management information module.

juniMRouterAgent.contactinfo: Juniper Networks, Inc. Postal: 10 Technology Park Drive Westford, MA 01886-3146 USA Tel: +1 978 589 5800 E-mail: mib@Juniper.net
juniMRouterAgent.description: The agent capabilities definitions for the multicast router component of the SNMP agent in the Juniper E-series family of products.

juniMRouterAgentV1.name: juniMRouterAgentV1
juniMRouterAgentV1.productrelease:
Version 1 of the multicast router component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.
        This version of the multicast router component was supported in JUNOSe
        4.1 and subsequent 4.x system releases.
juniMRouterAgentV1.description: The MIBs supported by the SNMP agent for the multicast router application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when support was added for the Juniper-MROUTER-MIB.

juniMRouterAgentV2.name: juniMRouterAgentV2
juniMRouterAgentV2.productrelease:
Version 2 of the multicast router component of the JUNOSe SNMP agent.
        These capabilities became obsolete when support was added to Juniper-MROUTER-MIB
        This version of the multicast router component is supported in the
        Juniper JUNOSe 5.0 and subsequent system releases upto 8.0.0.
juniMRouterAgentV2.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the multicast router application in JUNOSe. These capabilities became obsolete when juniMRouteConfGroup support was added to Juniper-MROUTER-MIB.

juniMRouterAgentV3.description: The MIB supported by the SNMP agent for the multicast router application in JUNOSe.These capabilities became obsolete when juniMcastGlobalConfGroup support was added to Juniper-MROUTER-MIB.
